abstract: The U.S. Senate on Thursday unanimously passed a resolution that recognizes as a genocide the mass killings of Armenians a century ago, a historic move that infuriated Turkey and dealt a blow to the already problematic ties between Ankara and Washington.
snippet: The U.S. Senate on Thursday unanimously passed a resolution that recognizes as a genocide the mass killings of Armenians a century ago, a historic move that infuriated Turkey and dealt a blow to the already problematic ties between Ankara and Wash...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. Senate on Thursday unanimously passed a resolution that recognizes as a genocide the mass killings of Armenians a century ago, a historic move that infuriated Turkey and dealt a blow to the already problematic ties between Ankara and Washington.
headline_main: U.S. Senate Passes Resolution Recognizing Armenian Genocide, Angering Turkey
headline_print_headline: U.S. Senate Passes Resolution Recognizing Armenian Genocide, Angering Turkey

abstract: The U.S. Senate on Thursday confirmed the nomination of John Sullivan, President Donald Trump's pick to be Ambassador to Russia, at a time when ties between Washington and Moscow have been strained.
snippet: The U.S. Senate on Thursday confirmed the nomination of John Sullivan, President Donald Trump's pick to be Ambassador to Russia, at a time when ties between Washington and Moscow have been strained.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. Senate on Thursday confirmed the nomination of John Sullivan, President Donald Trump's pick to be Ambassador to Russia, at a time when ties between Washington and Moscow have been strained.
headline_main: U.S. Senate Confirms John Sullivan as Next U.S. Ambassador to Russia
headline_print_headline: U.S. Senate Confirms John Sullivan as Next U.S. Ambassador to Russia

abstract: The U.S. Federal Trade Commission is considering asking a court to stop Facebook Inc from moving ahead with plans to integrate its WhatsApp, Instagram and Messenger subsidiaries, The Wall Street Journal reported on Thursday, citing people familiar with the matter.
snippet: The U.S. Federal Trade Commission is considering asking a court to stop Facebook Inc from moving ahead with plans to integrate its WhatsApp, Instagram and Messenger subsidiaries, The Wall Street Journal reported on Thursday, citing people familiar...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - The U.S. Federal Trade Commission is considering asking a court to stop Facebook Inc from moving ahead with plans to integrate its WhatsApp, Instagram and Messenger subsidiaries, The Wall Street Journal reported on Thursday, citing people familiar with the matter.
headline_main: U.S. Regulator Weighs Action Against Facebook Over How Its Apps Interact: Report
headline_print_headline: U.S. Regulator Weighs Action Against Facebook Over How Its Apps Interact: Report

abstract: An Italian judge on Thursday upheld an appeal by far-right group Casapound against a decision by Facebook to close its account, deeming that the move by the social media company prevented political pluralism.
snippet: An Italian judge on Thursday upheld an appeal by far-right group Casapound against a decision by Facebook to close its account, deeming that the move by the social media company prevented political pluralism.
lead_paragraph: ROME — An Italian judge on Thursday upheld an appeal by far-right group Casapound against a decision by Facebook to close its account, deeming that the move by the social media company prevented political pluralism.
headline_main: Italian Judge Orders Facebook to Reopen Neo-Fascist Group's Account
headline_print_headline: Italian Judge Orders Facebook to Reopen Neo-Fascist Group's Account

abstract: Italy's Fashion Chamber (CNMI) announced on Thursday a collaboration with the British Fashion Council which will bring part of London's Fashion week to Milan's men's fall-winter collections in January.
snippet: Italy's Fashion Chamber (CNMI) announced on Thursday a collaboration with the British Fashion Council which will bring part of London's Fashion week to Milan's men's fall-winter collections in January.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Italy's Fashion Chamber (CNMI) announced on Thursday a collaboration with the British Fashion Council which will bring part of London's Fashion week to Milan's men's fall-winter collections in January.
headline_main: Milan and London Fashion Weeks Join Forces With Anti-Brexit Message
headline_print_headline: Milan and London Fashion Weeks Join Forces With Anti-Brexit Message

abstract: The Trump administration imposed sanctions Thursday on a son of Nicaraguan President Daniel Ortega for his alleged role on money laundering and corruption.
snippet: The Trump administration imposed sanctions Thursday on a son of Nicaraguan President Daniel Ortega for his alleged role on money laundering and corruption.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration imposed sanctions Thursday on a son of Nicaraguan President Daniel Ortega for his alleged role on money laundering and corruption.
headline_main: US Imposed Sanctions on Nicaragua President's Son
headline_print_headline: US Imposed Sanctions on Nicaragua President's Son

abstract: As the House takes another step toward impeaching President Trump, concern is increasing that trying to remove a president will become a more common partisan tool.
snippet: As the House takes another step toward impeaching President Trump, concern is increasing that trying to remove a president will become a more common partisan tool.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — It was a powerful congressional weapon deployed in only the most extreme cases, so explosive that lawmakers feared the wider damage it could do if used for the wrong reasons. Today, the filibuster is an everyday part of Senate business, standard operating procedure in a polarized world where the once rare has become commonplace.

abstract: Clint Eastwood’s take on the frenzied aftermath of the Olympic Park bombing is flawed and fascinating.
snippet: Clint Eastwood’s take on the frenzied aftermath of the Olympic Park bombing is flawed and fascinating.
lead_paragraph: On July 27, 1996, a homemade bomb exploded at Centennial Olympic Park in Atlanta, the host city for that year’s Summer Olympics. Two people died and 100 were hurt in the attack. It was carried out by an anti-abortion militant named Eric Rudolph, though he was not arrested until 2003, after he had bombed two women’s health clinics and a gay bar and spent five years as a fugitive in the woods of Appalachia.

abstract: Teenage comments in response to our recent writing prompts, and an invitation to join the ongoing conversation.
snippet: Teenage comments in response to our recent writing prompts, and an invitation to join the ongoing conversation.
lead_paragraph: In this week’s roundup of student comments on our writing prompts, we asked young people to weigh in on whether the United States owes reparations to the descendants of slaves, tell us what they wished they could learn in school, and reflect on their identities.

abstract: No new international military students will come to the United States for training until new screening procedures are in place, the Pentagon said Thursday in the wake of the deadly shooting last week by a Saudi Arabian aviation trainee at a Florida Navy base.
snippet: No new international military students will come to the United States for training until new screening procedures are in place, the Pentagon said Thursday in the wake of the deadly shooting last week by a Saudi Arabian aviation trainee at a Florid...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — No new international military students will come to the United States for training until new screening procedures are in place, the Pentagon said Thursday in the wake of the deadly shooting last week by a Saudi Arabian aviation trainee at a Florida Navy base.
headline_main: US Says No New Foreign Military Students Until Better Checks
headline_print_headline: US Says No New Foreign Military Students Until Better Checks
